yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> as well as you=E2=80=99d expect</a>:</p><blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Outside the airport, I approach a dozen cab drivers =
who are chatting and waiting for fares. I pop the question: =E2=80=9CWill y=
ou take my Bitcoin?=E2=80=9D Two throw up their arms and walk away. One say=
s he knows a guy who does, but he=E2=80=99s not here. The rest ignore me an=
d continue their conversations.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I go with a=
 driver in a white Toyota van. He=E2=80=99ll take me to my hotel for $30=E2=
=80=94actual, not digital dollars. =E2=80=9CMost people prefer cash, and al=
most no one asks if they can pay in Bitcoin,=E2=80=9D says Saul Escobar, 55=
. =E2=80=9CThe system fails a lot, and lately it=E2=80=99s been really slow=
. There was a lot of enthusiasm last year, but it=E2=80=99s died down.=E2=
=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the hour it takes to exit the air=
port and reach my hotel, the Bitcoin in my phone falls 2% in value. I decid=
e to stop checking.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I feel lik=
e =E2=80=9CBitcoin is digital cash that people will be able to use for regu=
lar real-world transactions=E2=80=9D was a thing people said a few years ag=
o that has now gone entirely out of fashion. =E2=80=9CBitcoin is digital go=
ld that people will use as a store of value, a speculative asset and perhap=
s an inflation hedge=E2=80=9D is now the respectable position, and perfectl=
y compatible with being bullish on Bitcoin. It was a weird throwback for El=
 Salvador to make Bitcoin legal tender=C2=A0<em>last year</em>, after every=
one had moved on from the Bitcoin-is-useful-money idea. And now you see why=
 everyone moved on.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" =
